B	The facility's Evacuation Manager will assume the role of the Planning Chief unless the IC can fill these positions or he/she is moved to the Unified IC Position. He/she assesses possible hazards both direct and indirect to human health and/or the environment or property both inside and outside of the plant 


VIII	TERMINATION AND FOLLOW-UP ACTIVITIES

A	Incident Documentation/Reporting Requirements

1.	A written report may be required to be submitted to the Chelan County Local Emergency Planning Committee, Department of Ecology and the National Response Center, as soon as practicable, after the initial reporting of an NH3 release. The agency will advise you if they need a written report.

2.	This written report should include:

¿	The name, address and telephone number of the individual that reported the release;


¿	The name, address and telephone number of the individual submitting the report;

¿	The source of the release;

¿	The location of the release, as follows:

a	For  discharge  on land  or into air,  the name of the 			site,  the  street  address,  the  municipality  and the 			county of facility involved; or

b	For discharge on, under or into water,  the  name  of 			the  water body,  the latitude  and  longitude  of  the 			place the discharge  originated and a map identifying 			the areas affected by the discharge.

¿	The chemical name and Chemical Abstract Service (CAS) Number of each of the hazardous substances discharged     (CAS Number for NH3 is 7664-41-7); 

